description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Staff Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RSCN/RN [Child Branch]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time 37.5 hrs per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Children’s Emergency Department, Lewisham&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Children and Young People&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting and challenging opportunity has arisen for a dynamic individual with excellent clinical skills and ED experience to enhance their skills as a band 6 in ED.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate would take charge in the busy ED on a shift by shift basis and also be expected to work streaming/TW shifts to enhance the skill mix at triage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Band 6 nurse you will be responsible for the day to day flow of the department by ensuring the standards of care are met for children and their family / carers whilst in the emergency department, including delegation and deployment of the nursing team in the absence of a band 7.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for managing the shift ensuring the safety of both patients and their families and the nursing team, teaching both nursing students and qualified nurses, escalation of concerns as per department policy and working towards targets such as the 4 hour breach. Responsibilities also include liaising with the multidisciplinary team and providing leadership to nursing colleagues. You will be expected to have excellent clinical and communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be able to work all shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Laura Crome (Interim Matron) 02083333138 or 02083333000 bleep 4600, Candia St Clair or Clare Gray (Sisters) 02083333138 for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
